description = "Mume readability - directions. Two concerns. (1) Movement lines: '<name> leaves <dir>' keeps the mover name in the default colour, dims 'leaves' to dark grey, and tints the direction word + travel arrow muted teal (north ▲ south ▼ east ► ◄ west up ⇑ down ⇓); '<name> has arrived from the <dir>.' tints the from-direction teal, and the same sub also catches the directionless portal form '<name> has arrived.'. (2) The room Exits line: label dark grey, the whole direction list in muted teal (door parens included). Teal is muted so exits read below room mobs. Examples below are a live tt++ render."

example_before = [
